rComments: great prof, has a sense of humour and uses tons of examples from his clinical work. Lectures are pretty important if you dont read the textbook because he has no notes online. exams were fair and reflected material. he does tent to rant abut irrelevant or offensive things sometimes but it just makes everything more interesting!

He an older teacher. He knows his stuff. He prepares you well for the final exams. All of his mid-terms are compilation of EVERYTHING you`ve learned so far. He welcomes questions. He`s a good french teacher to have.

LOVE him, fav prof. used a lot of cool facts, examples from his clients. super easy exams even if you jsut read the text and don't go, but i loved his lectures. i highly recommend him, favorite class and favorite prof. very enthusiastic and humorous i learnt a lot from him. all from the text though

Interesting lectures sometimes, as he uses examples from former clients. However, the lectures involve him walking in late, opening the textbook, asking a student which class this is, and then going through the textbook page by page. I'm scared for the final, which is written by the department and will probably have covered much more material.
Just spews from the text book and is extremely offensive at times

He's a great professor. I got an A+ in his class! His tests are difficult, but he bell curves the marks to compensate. I really like how he used examples from his experience as a clinical psychologist.
great at explaining key terms. no need to go to class, just read the book! also, i found him very offensive.. makes inappropriate comments.

I'm a good student and attend 100% of class.  His exams are out of this world difficult.  When requested assistance with exams, overheard him joking with TA regarding my request.  Interesting class but exams don't CLEARLY reflect course material. Despite my efforts, I only passed because the final was standardized designed by the course coordinator

Absolutely love this prof! Keeps the lectures very entertaining so that I want to come to class! The fact that he draws from his line of work makes it seem as though what I'm learning is actually useful!

He is great! He is a very fun and funny prof. He keeps class entertaining and makes learning this stuff fun and interesting. He is a very nice guy and actually cares about people. I would definitely like to have him as a prof again!

Wonderful professor!! I have taken two classes with him and enjoyed them a lot. Yes, his lectures are based on the text, but he brings a lot of examples from his practice which makes classes very interesting. I would definetely recommend taking classes with this professor.

no need to attend classes to get a good grade, just read the texbook. prof is funny but very akward. he explains well the important things in texbook. Very good teacher only thing that bugs me is that, although he is obviously francophone, he has problems with masculin/feminin.He always says things like: LE table, or LA chat, which I find annoying

Great prof! Doesn't post his notes, but writes them in class; very easy to follow. Lots of interesting stories from his personal clinical experience. He enjoys his own jokes :) An easy A if you read the textbook.

2 words: Easy A!!!!! This prof is da bomb lol. His tests are a breeze you do not even need to attend lectures just read the txtbook. Reading the textbook felt more like pleasure reading than dry reading too so that makes it easier.

He likes to think his jokes and analogies are really funny and interesting, but they're not. His classes are pretty much useless, because all he does is read the book as if his students were still in grade school. His exams are really easy though, and you can get a great mark by just reading the textbook and not going to class :)

Very good teacher fun to listen to....Makes classes entertaining! Don't even need to go to class, just read the book, since the exam is 100% based on the textbook. Second time i have him and im very happy!

Lectures are not boring, very interesting and his little anecdotes about his patients are really fun to listen to! so cute when he makes jokes I just wanna give him a great big hug. bottom line, psych is all about reading the text book..nothing to do with the prof.

He is very fun! Actually, I am not interested in Psychology, but I could enjoy his classes. However, I hate the exam style… All PSY 1102 courses have common MC exams, and it has 100 questions in final exam. It sucks. But Prof. is excrement!! Thank you!!
good overall, explains well and his anecdotes are good (a lot about his mother in law, lol) he does read from the book basically so you could not attend class and still do good by studying the book.

Very engaging prof. Follows the textbook very strictly, so it's possible to get a good mark by studying the textbook (very well-written and engaging as well) and skipping all lectures, but the lectures are worth going to for the anecdotes alone.
A really good prof. Made class very interesting with his funny anecdotes and is very good at relating key ideas to real life.
